Name: Freeport
Notes: Practically lawless habitat, ruled by whichever crime boss has the most influence at the time. Tradition demands completely non-violent solutions to conflicts, oddly.

Name: Westfall
Notes: Ruled by popular dictator; Scout Service are interested in exotic plants and animals found in world's jungles. Hampered by the fact that anagathics are taboo

Name: Rust
Notes: Small desert colony primarily operates by salvaging tech and information from ancient ruins; Those with technical skills have the most power. Duels and trials by combat common

Name: Footfall
Notes: Subsector Scout HQ; regularly sends expeditions to the western subsector. People who don't look like spacers tend to be mocked.

Name: Romanus
Notes: Population somehow modified to live in hostile conditions, in spite of local TL being Renaissance-era. Scout Service studies ongoing. Technological discoveries surprisingly rapid.

Name: Oxide
Notes: Small colony primarily operates by salvaging tech and information from ancient ruins; Those with technical skills have the most power. Physical and combat prowess held in regard; those who look incapable of defending themselves are fair game.

Name: Eden
Notes: Prison colony operated by Taranis Corporation. Children are raised by the corporation and often shipped offworld.

Name: Freerock
Notes: Tiny planetoid operated by prospectors from Freeport; Rather more regulated due to Imperial presence, but taboos against violence are still in force.

Name: Lagoon
Bases: Gas Giant, Navy, Research, TAS, Consulate
Notes: Subsector capital, ruled by exceptionally popular governor; Entire world consists of beautiful islands in a cobalt ocean. The locals are obsessed with looking faaabulous.
